\begin_layout Standard
X-ray powder diffraction is a fast and simple technique to analyze materials
 on their crystal structure and chemical composition.
 This experiment applies the Debye-Scherrer method to determine crystal
 structure and lattice parameter of table salt NaCl and Aluminum Al in powdered
 form.
 X-rays, generated in a X-ray tube are directed at the sample, and the diffracte
d rays are collected with a movable detector.
 The results are useful for any experiments, where the crystallographic
 properties of NaCl or Al are needed; e.g.
 angle-resolved photoemission spectroscopy to determine the electronic band
 structure.
\end_layout

