\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 in Fig.
\begin_inset Formula $\,$
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:sample1"

\end_inset

 associated to the yet unknown 
\begin_inset Formula $h_{i}k_{i}l_{i}\,$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{1}$
\end_inset

 is the fist visible angle 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 in the same plot corresponding to some 
\begin_inset Formula $h_{1}k_{1}l_{1}$
\end_inset

 depending on the proposed lattice.
 Additionally, with 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:quotient"

\end_inset

 we made the assumption of having a cubic lattice (derivation found in 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
cite{xray}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, Section 3.5).
